<TITLE> 3 die in motor bike accident </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Jhalokati, May 1 (bdnews24.com) Three youths died in a road accident in Jhalokati on Saturday. The accident occurred when a bus and a motor bike had a head-on collision at Amirabad area at Jhalokati-Barisal highway at around 10am. The dead are Shovon Saha, 31, his friend Biddyut Kundu of Katpatti area in Jhalokathi, 29, and Shuman, 28, of Agarbari area in Jhalokati. The police said that Shovon and Biddyut had hired motor bike and were on their way to Barisal. When they reached at Amirabad, the motor bike and a bus of Suravi Paribahan, had a head-on collision. The police said that Shovon and the motor bike driver had died on the spot. Biddyut had died on the way to the hospital. The police said that the bodies had been handed over to their families after post mortem. The driver and helper of the bus managed to flee. bd
